getDefaultDriver.name: getDefaultDriver
getDefaultDriver.short_desc: Get the default session driver name.

setDefaultDriver.name: setDefaultDriver
setDefaultDriver.short_desc: Set the default session driver name.

extend.name: extend
extend.short_desc: Register a custom driver creator Closure.

isValidId.name: isValidId
isValidId.short_desc: Determine if this is a valid session ID.

invalidate.name: invalidate
invalidate.long_desc:
Clears all session attributes and flashes and regenerates the
session and deletes the old session from persistence.
invalidate.hint_desc: True if session invalidated, false if error

lifetime.name: lifetime
lifetime.short_desc:
Sets the cookie lifetime for the session cookie. A null value
                     will leave the system settings unchanged, 0 sets the cookie
                     to expire with browser session. Time is in seconds, and is
                     not a Unix timestamp.

migrate.name: migrate
migrate.short_desc:
Migrates the current session to a new session id while maintaining all
session attributes.
migrate.hint_desc: True if session migrated, false if error

destroy.name: destroy
destroy.short_desc: Whether to delete the old session or leave it to garbage collection

lifetime.name: lifetime
lifetime.short_desc:
Sets the cookie lifetime for the session cookie. A null value
                      will leave the system settings unchanged, 0 sets the cookie
                      to expire with browser session. Time is in seconds, and is
                      not a Unix timestamp.

save.name: save
save.short_desc: Force the session to be saved and closed.
save.long_desc:
This method is generally not required for real sessions as
the session will be automatically saved at the end of
code execution.

ageFlashData.name: ageFlashData
ageFlashData.short_desc: Age the flash data for the session.

has.name: has
has.short_desc: Checks if an attribute is defined.
has.hint_desc: true if the attribute is defined, false otherwise

default.name: default
default.short_desc: The default value if not found

pull.name: pull
pull.short_desc: Get the value of a given key and then forget it.

hasOldInput.name: hasOldInput
hasOldInput.short_desc: Determine if the session contains old input.

getOldInput.name: getOldInput
getOldInput.short_desc: Get the requested item from the flashed input array.

put.name: put
put.short_desc: Put a key / value pair or array of key / value pairs in the session.

push.name: push
push.short_desc: Push a value onto a session array.

increment.name: increment
increment.short_desc: Increment the value of an item in the session.

decrement.name: decrement
decrement.short_desc: Decrement the value of an item in the session.

flash.name: flash
flash.short_desc: Flash a key / value pair to the session.

now.name: now
now.short_desc:
Flash a key / value pair to the session
for immediate use.

flashInput.name: flashInput
flashInput.short_desc: Flash an input array to the session.

reflash.name: reflash
reflash.short_desc: Reflash all of the session flash data.

keep.name: keep
keep.short_desc: Reflash a subset of the current flash data.

remove.name: remove
remove.hint_desc: The removed value or null when it does not exist

forget.name: forget
forget.short_desc: Remove one or many items from the session.

flush.name: flush
flush.short_desc: Remove all of the items from the session.

isStarted.name: isStarted
isStarted.short_desc: Checks if the session was started.

registerBag.name: registerBag
registerBag.short_desc: Registers a SessionBagInterface with the session.

getBag.name: getBag
getBag.short_desc: Gets a bag instance by name.

getBagData.name: getBagData
getBagData.short_desc: Get the raw bag data array for a given bag.

previousUrl.name: previousUrl
previousUrl.short_desc: Get the previous URL from the session.

setPreviousUrl.name: setPreviousUrl
setPreviousUrl.short_desc: Set the "previous" URL in the session.

setExists.name: setExists
setExists.short_desc: Set the existence of the session on the handler if applicable.

getHandler.name: getHandler
getHandler.short_desc: Get the underlying session handler implementation.

handlerNeedsRequest.name: handlerNeedsRequest
handlerNeedsRequest.short_desc: Determine if the session handler needs a request.

setRequestOnHandler.name: setRequestOnHandler
setRequestOnHandler.short_desc: Set the request on the handler instance.
